        "QUESTION 1\n",
        "A method is just a normal function inside a class that you call yourself, while a magic method is a special method (with double underscores) that Python runs automatically when something happens.\n",
        "\n",
        "For example, in the Point class, distance_origin() is a normal method because you have to call it yourself using something like p1.distance_origin(). But methods like __init__ and __str__ are magic methods. You don’t call them directly — __init__ runs when you create the object, and __str__ runs when you print it. There is also __lt__, which is used automatically when comparing or sorting points.\n",
        "\n",
        "So basically, the difference is that normal methods are called by you, while magic methods are triggered automatically by Python."
      ],
